{
  "description": "A ground-up port of QuantLib (the C++ quantitative-finance library) into idiomatic Rust, delivered as a core library (libitofin) with thin language bindings planned (Python first, then a C ABI). Early-stage: the foundational EPIC-0 layer (types, errors, observer/observable patterns, handles, settings, utilities) plus core math primitives are in place, not yet usable for pricing.",
